<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684857>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 15. Cossura queenslandensis n. sp. Light microscopy. A–D, compound microscope; E–L, stereomicroscope; D, H–I, stained with methylen blue. (A) W.199308, general dorsal view; (B) W.199308, same specimen, anterior end, dorsal view; (C) W.199308, same specimen,pygidium;(D) W.16477, parapodium of chaetiger 37; (E) W.199308, general view, anterior part from lateral,middle from ventral, posterior from dorsal; (F) W.199308, another specimen, general ventral view; (G) W.16432, anterior end, dorsal view; (H) W.13222; anterior region, lateral view; (I) W.16477, anterior end, lateral view; (J–L) W.199308, pygidium. Scale bars: A, E, F = 500 μm, B–D, G = 100 μm, H, I = 300 μm, J–L = 200 μm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4684857/files/figure.png" .

